title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return user recognizable strings
OB: When calling the function IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction, the labels returned are null. However, after data extraction, the labels are recognizable strings.
EB: The function IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should return recognizable strings even before data extraction.
SR: To reproduce the issue, call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before and after data extraction and observe the difference in the returned labels.
